-- China's Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region to issue 5.5 bln yuan of municipal bonds 
-- By the Shanghai Newsroom and Fayen Wong
-- Mon Aug 04, 2014 04:15AM EDT
-- None



SHANGHAI, August 4 (Reuters) - China's Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region will issue a total of 5.5 billion yuan ($889.9 million) of five-, seven- and 10-year municipal bonds on August 11, according to an announcement posted on a website for major Chinese bond issues.

Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region is the fifth local government to issue municipal bonds. For more details, click on www.chinabond.com.cn The Ministry of Finance said in late May that 10 local governments had been given quotas to issue a combined 109.2 billion yuan of municipal bonds this year. [ID:nB9N0NA02D] The ministry has also allowed selected local governments to directly issue and redeem their own bonds to help tackle a $3 trillion public debt problem, launching China's first-ever municipal bond market. Governments in Shanghai, Zhejiang, Guangdong, Shenzhen, Jiangsu, Shandong, Beijing, Qingdao, Ningxia and Jiangxi are included in the pilot scheme. [ID:nL3N0O710I]